meta {
  name: Get Possible Edge Mappings
  type: http
  seq: 5
}

get {
  url: {{host}}/agent-playground/graphs/:graph_id/versions/:version_id/nodes/:node_id/possible-edge-mappings/
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

params:path {
  graph_id: {{graph_id}}
  version_id: {{version_id}}
  node_id: {{node_id}}
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

vars:pre-request {
  node_id: 51fbb228-5e25-59bb-a001-7e858fb57574
  graph_id: 8da2b6d9-fded-468d-9cff-821cefa1cecf
  version_id: 0b8b2ded-9988-453d-b4b6-e9dd59a06055
}

docs {
  # Get Possible Edge Mappings

  Returns all source nodes that have NodeConnections targeting this node, along with their output ports.

  This endpoint helps the frontend determine what edges can be created by showing:
  - Which nodes are connected at the NodeConnection level
  - What output ports are available on those source nodes
  - The NodeConnection IDs for reference

  ## Path Parameters
  - `graph_id`: Graph UUID
  - `version_id`: Graph version UUID
  - `node_id`: Target node UUID

  ## Response

  Returns an array of source nodes, each containing:
  - `source_node_id`: UUID of the source node
  - `source_node_name`: Name of the source node
  - `node_connection_id`: UUID of the NodeConnection between source and target
  - `output_ports`: Array of all output ports on the source node

  ### Example Response
  ```json
  {
    "status": true,
    "result": [
      {
        "source_node_id": "51fbb228-5e25-59bb-a001-7e858fb57579",
        "source_node_name": "Text Processor",
        "node_connection_id": "8da2b6d9-fded-468d-9cff-821cefa1cecf",
        "output_ports": [
          {
            "id": "bda62703-6788-41c1-b103-1cd9a56f6677",
            "key": "response",
            "display_name": "result",
            "direction": "output",
            "data_schema": {"type": "string"},
            "required": true,
            "default_value": null,
            "metadata": {},
            "ref_port_id": null
          },
          {
            "id": "cda62703-6788-41c1-b103-1cd9a56f6678",
            "key": "custom",
            "display_name": "metadata",
            "direction": "output",
            "data_schema": {"type": "object"},
            "required": false,
            "default_value": null,
            "metadata": {},
            "ref_port_id": null
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
  ```

  ## Use Cases

  1. **Edge Creation UI**: When user wants to create an edge to a node, show available source ports
  2. **Connection Validation**: Check if NodeConnection exists before allowing edge creation
  3. **Port Selection**: Display source nodes and ports in a dropdown/list for edge creation

  ## Notes
  - Only returns nodes with active NodeConnections (soft-deleted connections excluded)
  - Returns all output ports regardless of existing edges (frontend can filter)
  - Empty array if node has no incoming NodeConnections
  - Ports are ordered by display_name
}
